Sep 6 2009 	Best hote of our trip	Have read a few of the reviews and am surprised at the negative comments... we were obviously very lucky as our room was fab and just what we wanted for a one-night stay. We had booked a de-luxe room for 3 people (mum, dad and teenage son) and our confirmation gave us a location in the Forum Tower. On arrival (self-parked, so we were miles from the reception area and ended up going in via the staff entrance!) we had to go through miles of slot machines (we understand the concept!) until we got to the reception area. Check in was relatively quick, despite queues, and we had a friendly check-in clerk who upgraded us to Augustus Tower. Not sure why and we did'nt question it... but presumably a good move as we had a lovely, very clean, very comfortable room with lots of luxury extras. Views over the Strip, two comfortable beds with great linen, sofa and chairs, two windows, massive TV, mini-bar (which we didn't use - and there were no prices), fab bathroom with double shower and spa bath, separate loo, great toileteries. We did Las Vegas for our son - and spent our evening wandering the hotel and streets for the atmosphere. Ceasars made it acceptable for us &quot;oldies&quot; - however the pool was full of mostly &quot;stag&quot; and &quot;hen&quot; parties (lots of cocktails and beer on the go and lots of heavy flirting). We enjoyed the facilities, but thought the pool was a bit mucky because of plastic cups, fag ends etc especially after the odd gust of wind. The best margarhitas of the trip though!If you're going to book, then make sure you spend a little extra... however, think this is a general problem in Las Vegas as we went to visit Circus Circus (again for our son) and found that incredibly &quot;tired&quot;.However we did have the most amazing &quot;all you can eat&quot; buffets in one of the restaurants - think it was Cafe Lago - which satisfied our requirements on the night. Definitely not a Michelin starred experience, but a great way to get good value and good food, with pretty good service too. Alcoholic drinks were expensive but the sodas were OK.	
