Aug 30 2009 	Many better hotels in Vegas	We have just got back from a three-night stay at Caesar's Palace staying in one of the recently refurbished rooms in the Forum Tower. Having visited Vegas over 10 times we both agreed that this stay was probably the most disappointing visit we have had. Let's start with the room, refurbished and spacious yet the corridors were dirty and the cleaning trolley was permanently parked outside our room - nice! The room itself had the handle hanging off one of the cupboards, the main light in the bathroom was not working, the fan in the toilet was permanently on (not great for sleeping) and the air conditioning started making a very strange noise after being on for a little time and the only way to stop it was to switch it off, so no air con when sleeping.The location of the hotel is fantastic, right in the middle of everything. Restaurants were all very good (especially the Mesa Grill) although all somewhat expensive compared to our previous trips.Regarding the Total Rewards card and the comps, we were both a little surprised at how little we were comped against our room bill. Having stayed at other casinos in the past this was certainly not our experience,All we can conclude is that Caesar's is trading on it's history and is in a position of strength therefore does not need to take much care nor does it need to do much to attract visitors. We will not be returning again to Caesar's - plenty more choice available elsewhere offering much better value.	
