Aug 11 2009 	Awesome experience!	My husband and I travel to Las Vegas 2-3 times a year and this is the first time we chose to stay at Caesar's Palace. Caesar's is a 5-star hotel/casino which has been around longer than others but has never lost it's class. We stayed in the Forum Tower and the location was perfect. We were close to the casino action, forum shops and restaurants. Our room overlooked the strip but was very quiet and secluded. The decor was contemporary and the room was spotless. Housekeeping never failed to clean our room promptly and always left extra amenities, towels, etc. The casino has a good layout and plenty of slots and table games. The cocktail waitresses are excellent when you're at the table games but can be spotty when you're at the slots. The mimosas and mojitas are excellent! The table games have higher limits during the weekends but we wandered directly across the street to O'Sheas where they have low table limits and they honor the &quot;Total Rewards&quot; players cards. The restaurants can be a bit pricey but the food is A-plus with large portions. Overall we had a great experience and will definately stay at Caesar's Palace in the future.	
