May 22 2009	Caesar's Palace Las Vegas May 2009	We had a mixed experience with Caesar's during a visit from May 9-13th. We were making out first trip to Caesars (we usually stay at MGM Grand) and were there to celebrate our 25th anniversary. I checked many postings here before we left and was concerned about the situation at the pool and the construction. They had two pools open but for our intents only one since the other was &quot;european&quot; (topless). The pool was very crowded since it was the only one for the hotel, but worse than that was the construction that surrounded the pool on 2 of 4 sides. The noise and unsightly view lowered the satisfaction of the pool time a great deal. It was just plain ugly to look at.In addition we were hoping for the nice upgrade offers that we had read about, especially in light of it being our anniversary. We had notified the hotel ahead of time of this fact. There were three couples in our party (all arriving seperately). One couple got a free upgrade with little effort at all (and no tip required). The second got an upgrade for $40 a night. We were offered an upgrade (with a tip) for $50 a night. We declined their offer. This left a bad taste in our mouth. The people working the casino were very nice for the most part, and the store employees were very nice and helpful. The front desk just took away all the good will of the others.We will not go back to Caesars. Next stop, either back to MGM or maybe try the Mirage. Caesar's, not so much......	
May 22 2009 	Enjoyed our stay here very much	This is now the third time that we have stayed in Caesars Palace so you can see that we do like it. I feel that I should now give feedback to counteract some of the negative comments that others have left (although I do not dispute that they received poor service.) We booked the room through an online booking agency and the voucher said that the room would be 'allocated on arrival'. When we arrived I asked how much it would cost for an upgrade as I wanted to stay in the Palace Tower (where we had stayed the last time). The receptionist said that the room we had been allocated was in that tower anyway! I felt that we got a fantastic deal - the room had 2 interconnecting bathrooms, was beautifully furnished and was spotlessly clean. The hotel is big and impersonal but so are many of the other hotels in Las Vegas. The situation in the middle of the strip is excellent and you are within walking distance of many of the other large hotels. We also toured around Arizona and for our last night returned to Las Vegas as we were flying out the following morning. This time I booked on the Caesars Palace website and got a deal for a hotel room and 2 tickets for Elton John. This time the room was in the newly refurbished Forum Tower and it was very nice as well, although I still prefer the Palace Tower. This room was convenient for the show as it is just across the Forum Casino from the theatre. Would I stay here again if I went to Las Vegas? Yes - I personally have always found it to be very good value with lovely accommodation. The only disappointment was that the swimming pools closed early so don't leave it too late if you want to go for a swim!!	
