assment. Stay away.	
May 21 2009 	Great room amazing service	We stayed five nights in the Augustus Tower. The room was large, maid service prompt and the bathroom especially gorgeous. The best part, however, came after we left. We were just getting ready to board our plane when we discovered that we'd forgotten to pack stuff, mostly clothing, left in a nightstand, some of which would have been hard to replace. Called Caesar's minutes before takeoff, security immediately sent someone up to our room, confirmed to us that our stuff was safe and would be Fed Ex'd the same day. And it was. From the initial phone call, all this took place in a matter of four minutes as we boarded the plane. We're not high rollers, but with that kind of service, we felt like ones.	
