Apr 13 2009 	Great Stay As Always!	We stayed at Caesar's for three days, Thursday through Sunday. It was busy, as it was a holiday weekend, but even so we had a great stay. We were upgraded to Augutus Tower rooms, which were fantastic, and the staff was courteous and attentive. From the bell desk to the valets, everyone was friendly, helpful, and made our trip a memorable one.The mid-Strip location is amazing. It's tough to be in a better spot if you want to be right in the middle of the action. My only knock against Caesar's is that everything on the property is expensive, but this is true of most of the big megaresorts on the Strip. Get water, coffee, snacks, etc, outside of the resort to keep costs down. Even using the ATMs at Caesar's costs $5, so be prepared.Overall, I have to say that this is one of my favourite Vegas properties and I won't hesitate to stay there in the future.	
