Feb 12 2009 	Girlfriends' Weekend at Caesar's Palace	I was frankly a litle wary of staying at Caesar's Palace, based on many of the Trip Advisor reviews, but a girlfriend booked the trip, so off we went. I did pore over the many reviews available, and took the advice of so many, to absolutely not stay in the Roman Tower, and to ask for a room in the newest Augustus Tower instead. We checked in on Thursday, Feb 5, at around noon, and did not wait in line at all. Walked right up to the desk, handed the super friendly clerk a $20 with my drivers license and credit card and asked to be put in the Augustus Tower, Not only did we get a great room there, but we got one on the side of the Bellagio Fountain - lovely! The bathroom was huge, the linens were nice, and housekeeping gave us loads of extra towels. We spent a morning at the Qua Spa and got massages and facials. Very nice spa area. Massage was pretty good, and facial was fantastic. In the mornings, we went down to the Payard pastry and coffee shop and brought pastries, fresh fruit and coffee back to our room. Perfect, and way cheaper and less time consuming than a sit-down breakfast. We had fabulous meals at Bradley Ogden and Nero's, and a mediocre one at Rao's.Overall a nice hotel, and a very fun experience. Not the Four Seasons Hotel, by any means, but nowhere near the price of the Four Seasons, ether...	
